I'm setting the cookie and session timeout as follows (I need to use this API. I can't use the new Identity api. Please don't provide solutions based on Identity):

```
.AddCookie(options =>
{
    options.ExpireTimeSpan = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(15);
    options.SlidingExpiration = true;
    options.Cookie.MaxAge = options.ExpireTimeSpan;
})
.AddOpenIdConnect(options =>
{
     options.MaxAge = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(15);
     ...
});
```

This sets the same timeout for every user. And these values are set before the user is redirected to the IDP.

How can I update both the cookie and session timeout to different values once the user has logged in (but before the cookie is returned to the UI). I'm authenticating against Azure B2C and would like to use the user's role to determine the timeout.

I'm hoping there is an event I can listen for that is passed information returned from Azure that would allow me to update the timeouts once the user has successfully logged in.

